# Multi-User Company Data Isolation Plan

Since `user_id` was originally designed to isolate different users' data, opening up the RLS to `USING (true)` means all users across the entire system see everyone's data. 

To allow a single company to have multiple users (e.g., an admin and an accountant) while keeping their data isolated from *other* companies, we need to link the accountant to the admin's `user_id`.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Proposed Concept:** We will designate the `user_id` of the `master` account as the main "Company ID". 
> 
> 1. We will add a `company_owner_id` column to the `employees` table.
> 2. The `master` employee record will have its `company_owner_id` set to its own `user_id`.
> 3. The `accountant` employee record will have its `company_owner_id` set to the `master`'s `user_id`.
> 4. All tables (receipts, orders, etc.) will use this `company_owner_id` to filter data, ensuring the accountant sees the exact same data as the master.

